<TITLE> New Biman MD takes over Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 16 (bdnews24.com)  Retired air commodore Zahed Kuddus has been appointed as the managing director and chief executive of Biman Bangladesh Airlines Limited. His appointment was finalised at a meeting of the Biman's Board of Directors with the chief adviser's special assistant in charge of the civil aviation and tourism ministry Mahbub Jamil in the chair on Tuesday. "Retired air commodore Zahed Kuddus has been appointed as the managing director and CEO of Biman in the meeting of Biman Board of Directors today (Tuesday). He would take over on Wednesday," Jamil told bdnews24.com after the meeting. "The new CEO showed ability of efficient management in the past. We hope Biman will run well under his leadership," the special assistant said. Kuddus served as the chairman of Civil Aviation Authority of Bangladesh (CAAB) from 2002 to 2005. Jamil said a chief executive may be hired from abroad once Biman goes into international partnership. Kuddus's predecessor Mohammad Abdul Momen was made joint secretary at the agriculture ministry on Sept 8. bdne
